Neither would I. Unless my car was meticulously paint (clearcoat) corrected and ceramic coated. Also hand washed and mini detailed once a week..by yours truly. Two to three hours every week. Engine bay too! Nobody but me washes my car. Ever. Always by hand using 5 wash mits. The soiled side (all ten of them) never goes back in the soap bucket. I will teach you how to properly wash a car some time.

UV damage in South Florida is brutal. I work nights and my car sits (covered) until 9PM. BTW, the paint is 100% scratch free and flawless. I am SO glad you posted your snarky concern. Dont stop assuming. It keeps us all amused.Ôªø

